---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About Emchi Tsundu Dolma"
  description="Learn about Emchi Tsundu Dolma — graduate of Men-Tsee-Khang, Dharamshala. 10+ years experience in Tibetan Medicine and Ayurveda, serving Werribee and Melbourne."
>
  <!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-hero-tibetan tibetan-script">གསོ་བའི་མཁས་པ།</p>
      <h1 class="page-hero-title">Emchi Tsundu Dolma</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-subtitle">Tibetan Medicine & Ayurveda Consultant</p>
    </div>
    <div class="page-hero-wave" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 1440 60" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <path d="M0,30 C360,60 1080,0 1440,30 L1440,60 L0,60 Z" fill="#F5F1E8"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main about section -->
  <section class="section" style="background: #F5F1E8;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-grid">

        <!-- Profile image side -->
        <div class="about-image-side reveal-left">
          <div class="about-image-wrap">
            <!-- Decorative background -->
            <div class="image-bg-circle" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <div class="image-placeholder" aria-label="Emchi Tsundu Dolma">
              <span class="image-placeholder-icon" aria-hidden="true">🌸</span>
              <span class="image-placeholder-text">Emchi Tsundu Dolma</span>
              <span class="image-placeholder-sub">Photograph coming soon</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Credentials -->
          <div class="credentials">
            <div class="credential reveal delay-1">
              <span class="cred-icon" aria-hidden="true">🎓</span>
              <div>
                <p class="cred-title">Men-Tsee-Khang Graduate</p>
                <p class="cred-desc">Dharamshala, India — Principal Institute of Tibetan Medicine</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="credential reveal delay-2">
              <span class="cred-icon" aria-hidden="true">⏳</span>
              <div>
                <p class="cred-title">10+ Years Experience</p>
                <p class="cred-desc">Traditional Tibetan Medicine & holistic healing</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="credential reveal delay-3">
              <span class="cred-icon" aria-hidden="true">📍</span>
              <div>
                <p class="cred-title">Based in Werribee, VIC</p>
                <p class="cred-desc">Monthly visits at Tara Institute, Melbourne</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Text content side -->
        <div class="about-text-side reveal-right">
          <h2 class="about-section-h">A Healer Rooted in Ancient Wisdom</h2>
          
          <div class="about-prose">
            <p>
              Emchi Tsundu Dolma is a compassionate and highly trained Tibetan Medicine practitioner who has dedicated her life to the ancient healing system of <strong>Sowa Rigpa</strong> — the science of healing. She graduated from <strong>Men-Tsee-Khang</strong>, the most respected institution of Tibetan Medicine in Dharamshala, India, where she received rigorous training in all aspects of traditional diagnosis and treatment.
            </p>

            <p>
              With over ten years of professional experience, Emchi combines the wisdom of Tibetan Medicine with complementary principles of Ayurveda, creating an integrative approach that addresses each patient as a whole person — body, mind, and spirit. Her practice is founded on the conviction that true healing arises when we understand and restore the natural balance unique to each individual.
            </p>

            <p>
              Emchi moved to Australia carrying this precious lineage of healing wisdom, driven by the desire to make authentic Tibetan Medicine accessible to those seeking a deeper, more holistic approach to wellbeing. She works primarily from Werribee, Victoria, and also visits Melbourne's Tara Institute on the first Saturday of each month.
            </p>

            <blockquote class="about-quote">
              <p>"True healing is not merely the absence of disease, but the restoration of balance and harmony within ourselves — and ultimately, within our relationship with the world."</p>
              <footer>— Emchi Tsundu Dolma</footer>
            </blockquote>

            <h3 class="about-section-h3">Philosophy of Healing</h3>
            <p>
              At the heart of Emchi's practice is the Medicine Buddha's aspiration: to become medicine, physician, and nurse to all who suffer. She approaches every patient with genuine curiosity, deep listening, and unwavering compassion — understanding that each person who walks through her door is not just a set of symptoms, but a complete human being with a unique story.
            </p>

            <p>
              She believes that healing is a collaborative journey. While she brings the diagnostic precision and therapeutic knowledge of Sowa Rigpa, the patient brings their commitment, openness, and trust. Together, they chart a course back to balance.
            </p>

            <h3 class="about-section-h3">Training & Education</h3>
            <ul class="about-list">
              <li>Graduate of Men-Tsee-Khang, Dharamshala, India</li>
              <li>Traditional Tibetan pulse diagnosis (rtsa brtag)</li>
              <li>Herbal medicine formulation according to classical texts</li>
              <li>External therapies: cupping, moxibustion, acupuncture, oil therapies</li>
              <li>Ayurvedic constitutional assessment and treatment</li>
              <li>10+ years clinical practice in Tibetan Medicine</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary about-cta" id="about-book-btn">
            Book a Consultation with Emchi →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Philosophy quote section -->
  <section class="section" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1B5E7F, #0F3D52); text-align: center;">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="philosophy-tibetan tibetan-script reveal">
        གནས་སྐབས་ཀྱི་དྲིན་གྱིས་མི་རྣམས་ནད་བདེ་ཐོབ་ཤོག།
      </p>
      <blockquote class="philosophy-quote reveal delay-1">
        <p>"As long as beings are sick, until their illness is cured, may I become the medicine, the physician, and the one who nurses and cares for them."</p>
        <footer>— Medicine Buddha Prayer (Sangye Menla)</footer>
      </blockquote>
      <a href="/services" class="btn btn-secondary reveal delay-2" id="about-services-btn">
        Explore Our Treatments →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1B5E7F, #0F3D52);
    padding: 5rem 0 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-hero-tibetan { font-size: 1.25rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); display: block; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-hero-title { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); color: white; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-hero-subtitle { color: #E8B44F; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.125rem; }
  .page-hero-wave { line-height: 0; }
  .page-hero-wave svg { width: 100%; height: 50px; display: block; }

  /* About grid */
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 380px 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* Image side */
  .about-image-wrap {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .image-bg-circle {
    position: absolute;
    inset: -16px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(27, 94, 127, 0.15) 0%, transparent 70%);
  }
  .image-placeholder {
    width: 320px;
    height: 380px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(27, 94, 127, 0.08), rgba(46, 139, 168, 0.12));
    border: 2px dashed rgba(27, 94, 127, 0.3);
    border-radius: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .image-placeholder-icon { font-size: 4rem; }
  .image-placeholder-text { font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 1rem; color: #1B5E7F; font-weight: 600; }
  .image-placeholder-sub  { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: #6B7A8D; }

  /* Credentials */
  .credentials { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .credential {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.875rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(189, 195, 199, 0.4);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(15, 61, 82, 0.06);
  }
  .cred-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .cred-title { font-weight: 600; color: #1B5E7F; font-size: 0.9375rem; }
  .cred-desc  { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: #6B7A8D; margin-top: 0.125rem; }

  /* Text side */
  .about-section-h {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    color: #1B5E7F;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .about-section-h3 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #1B5E7F;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .about-prose { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.125rem; }
  .about-prose p { color: #2C3E50; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.75; }
  .about-prose strong { color: #1B5E7F; }

  .about-quote {
    background: rgba(27, 94, 127, 0.05);
    border-left: 4px solid #F39C12;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }
  .about-quote p { font-style: italic; color: #2C3E50 !important; }
  .about-quote footer { margin-top: 0.625rem; color: #6B7A8D; font-size: 0.875rem; }

  .about-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .about-list li {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #2C3E50;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .about-list li::before {
    content: '✦';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #F39C12;
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    top: 0.35em;
  }

  .about-cta { margin-top: 2rem; }

  /* Philosophy section */
  .philosophy-tibetan { font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; display: block; }
  .philosophy-quote {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
    border-left: none;
    border-top: 2px solid rgba(243,156,18,0.4);
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .philosophy-quote p { font-style: italic; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .philosophy-quote footer { margin-top: 0.875rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 0.875rem; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
    .about-image-wrap { display: flex; justify-content: center; }
  }
</style>
